thread.title: ANA takes two 777-300ERs from GECAS

author: flightglobal.com
title: ANA takes two 777-300ERs from GECAS
text:
All Nippon Airways (ANA) has taken delivery of two Boeing 777-300ERs under a sale and leaseback deal with GE Capital Aviation Services (GECAS).
The aircraft are from an order for three 777-300ERs that ANA placed in 2013 and took delivery of from March through May, Ascend Fleets shows.
The 777s join a Boeing 767-300ER that ANA Cargo leases from GECAS.
ANA operates 22 777-300ERs, including the aircraft delivered by GECAS, Ascend shows.
